<br>
[----][----][----][----][----]<br>
My raid loot rules are as follows: <br>
<br>
i. Class armor (Non-BP) <br>
ii. Class BP <br>
iii. Class weapon <br>
iv. Major gems <br>
v. Blue diamonds <br>
vi. Cash loots <br>
<br>
Winning one item in a certain category prevents you from winning another in the same category until all in your class have won something in that category. <br>
<br>
This means if you win the wizard gloves, you cannot roll on the wizard helm until every other wizard has a base piece, but you can roll on the wizard robe or the wizard wand. Please remember this when you ask to sign up for a roll. If you win the ranger bracer and the much better ranger leggings drop later, you will NOT be able to roll for the legs unless all other rangers have one something in the interim. <br>
<br>
The first set of cash loots will go to raid leader to cover their costs for the raid. This could include such things as stones for Hate and Air, or coffins for impossible CRs. <br>
<br>
The second set of cash loots go to clerics. Each cleric will receive up to three pieces of cash loot worth at least 300 pp to cover their costs for peridots and what have you. <br>
<br>
After that cash loot is randomed to raid as its own category. <br>
[----][----][----][----][----]<br>
<br>
The point is, that is standard operating procedure what Gravethumb did.  In order to make the raid more fair for everyone that attends, you don't let the same person roll on each and every item.<br>
<br>
